Description:
Location, Luxury and Brand-New Style
Wonderfully quiet yet incredibly convenient, this stunning new townhouse presents an idyllic low-maintenance lifestyle with its clever design, first-class features and immediate access to everything that counts. Bathed in natural light, the home's meticulously detailed interior boasts three bedrooms (large master) all with built-in robes, deluxe ensuite, equally-stylish main bathroom and additional powder room (third WC). Add to this a well-appointed kitchen with breakfast bar, soft-close drawers, Baumatic cooking appliances and dishwasher, as well as an expansive open-plan living/dining area with stacker doors revealing a sunny terrace. Other highlights include split-system heating and cooling (all bedrooms and living area), ducted vacuum, stone benchtops throughout, hardwood floors, alarm and video intercom, plus a large laundry, under-stair storeroom, courtyard and double garage (r/c) with internal entry. In a prime location walking distance to Batman Station and Sydney Road trams, it's also close to primary and secondary schools, Coburg Lake, popular cafes and vibrant shopping precincts.
Insights: 82 Ross Street, Coburg VIC 3058 was last sold in 2018 and 146 other 3 bedroom house in Coburg have recently been sold.

Description:
Timeless Terrace Full of Surprises
In a terrific location with easy access to the best of cosmopolitan Coburg, this semi-detached Victorian presents a perfect inner-urban lifestyle opportunity with its generous design, quality enhancements and plenty of room to further expand (STCA). Beyond the Hawthorn-brick facade, discover a light-filled interior comprising two double bedrooms (both with BIRs) and updated bathroom, central lounge/dining through to the open living/meals area and new kitchen with tiled splashbacks and stainless steel cooking appliances. Other features include gas heating and split-system a/c, high ornate ceilings, new carpets and original timber floors, European laundry, plus a private north-facing backyard with extensive brick paving, established gardens and handy ROW access. Moments from Robinson Reserve, it's also walking distance to Moreland Station, Sydney Road trams and cafes, Coburg's renowned shopping precinct, close to popular schools and easy access to Citylink. Agent: Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Beckwith Beckons
After half a century in one family this attractively presented three bedroom home, on approximately 501m2 of land in an amazing location, has finally hit the market. Well-lit and with an inviting ambience, the double fronted abode is introduced by a wide street frontage and boasts beautifully big bedrooms, a central lounge room, kitchen and dining domain with freestanding gas stove, covered outdoor entertaining area with large lawn area. Bonuses include 3 metre high ceilings, architectural details, heating, cooling, a long side driveway, carport and sizeable workshop. Add your own touches and enhancements or consider creating something entirely new (Subject To Council Approval) in this highly convenient locale, a stroll to everything from trams to trains, cafes, schools, Coburg Market and Coburg Lake Reserve.

Description:
Period On Portland
Instant appeal with a suite of value-adding options to choose from, this charming home is a must-see for buyers and renovators alike with its functional design, distinctive features and substantial allotment complete with OSP. The first time offered in many decades, this loved family home provides a lifestyle of quality and comfort with scope to further enhance and expand (STCA). South of Bell Street in one of Coburg's favourite pockets, it's close to Munro Street buses, Coburg Station, local parks, schools, shops and supermarkets, Sydney Road trams, cafes and restaurants. Opportunity of a lifetime!

Elegance, Ease, Excellence

Contemporary, Convenient and Surprisingly Spacious
In a wonderfully quiet cul-de-sac location with the buzz of Sydney Road at the end of the street, this two-storey townhouse presents an idyllic inner-urban lifestyle/investment opportunity. On its own separate-titled block with no shared land, the home's light-filled interior comprises four generous bedrooms (three with BIRs), stylish ensuite and two-way main bathroom, expansive open-plan living/dining area complemented by a stone-bench kitchen with Smeg cooking appliances and dishwasher. Description:
Street Facing with no common property
A fantastic town house with its own street frontage and no owners' corporation or common property. The location speaks for itself - It is overlooking parkland, close to transport, the popular Reservoir West Primary & Newlands Primary schools, Coburg Hill shops/cafés and the Edwardes Street shopping precint, Edwardes Lake Park, Edgars creek and the Coburg Drive-ins.
Both levels of this great home are cleverly planned. Downstairs you will find; a lovely open plan living area and kitchen with space for a dining table, a great back yard with undercover entertaining area, single garage, laundry, and the 2nd WC.
While Upstairs has; Main bedroom with built in robes, split system air conditioner/heater and an undercover balcony ideal for sitting and relaxing and taking in the tranquillity of the great neighbourhood. The second bedroom also has a spilt system air conditioner/heater and built in robes. You will also find the main bathroom upstairs.
Located on the Coburg North/Preston/Reservoir borders, this property enjoys the best of what 3 rising suburbs have to offer.

Description:
UNDER OFFER
In Coburg's exclusive Moreland Park precinct, this landmark Victorian (c1890) presents a rare opportunity to secure one of the area's premier properties surrounded by landscaped gardens on well over 900sqm of land. An impressive refurbishment by award winning architects Edmond & Corrigan complemented by interior designer Naylor Booth & Associates, the home's grand interior showcases five bedrooms (master with ensuite) and home office/6BR, study/library, deluxe main bathroom and additional powder room (third WC). Add to this elegant formal lounge and dining rooms, central living room and open family/meals area enhanced by a first-class kitchen with stone-benchtops, Gaggenau cooking appliances and integrated dishwasher & walk in pantry. Other stand-out features include the home's signature tower and rooftop above with spectacular 360-degree views, plus hydronic heating, towering ceilings with ornate plasterwork, open fireplaces with original marble mantels, excellent storage spaces throughout, as well as a paved outdoor entertaining area, large storeroom/workshop, gorgeous gardens and two-car off-street parking. Walking distance to Nicholson Street/Moreland Road trams, primary and secondary schools, easy access to Moreland Station, Sydney Road shops, cafes and restaurants. Just imagine living here!

Description:
Definitively Deco With Exciting Future Prospects
Lovers of Art Deco design will revel in the generous proportions, striking ceilings and superb details that grace this effortlessly stylish three bedroom home. Immediately comfortable showcasing hardwood floors, decorative ceiling, picture rails and panelled doors this appealing home showcases a traditional layout with spacious lounge and dining flowing to a stylishly updated kitchen featuring stainless steel appliances and ample storage. The neat rear garden offers an outdoor space to enjoy while incorporating an original garage/workshop that effortlessly accommodates four cars. Add to this a pristine bathroom with claw foot tub, separate laundry and gas heater, moments to transport, Coburg North Primary, farmers market, local shopping, parks and bustling Sydney Road. Exciting now and with unlimited potential into the future on a 452m2 (approx.), this property offers families and investors a myriad of options moving forward, as a pristine rental or comfortable base from which to explore options for further enhancement, extension or possible redevelopment, STCA.

Description:
Top spot to shape the future
On approximately 470m2 in an attractive locale zoned to Strathmore College, this three bedroom Californian Bungalow style home offers an enticing opportunity to shape the future. Liveable now, yet welcoming inspiration and enhancement - or the construction of something entirely new (subject to council approval) - the home presents a spacious living room, which flows into a kitchen/dining with gas stove and air conditioner, plus a covered outdoor area suited to entertaining. Three double bedrooms share a central bathroom with a shower and separate bath, and extras include solar panels, front and rear lawns, a front carport and large garage/workshop adjoining a rear ROW. Schools, buses, Melville Road trams and Shore Reserve are within moments and cosmopolitan Sydney Road just a short drive.

This spacious one bedroom Villa Unit (approximately 8 squares) comprises a neat kitchen with gas appliances, spacious bedroom with built-in-robes, separate lounge, roomy bathroom / laundry with shower over bath and features polished floorboards, gas heating and split system air-conditioning.
In one of Coburg's finest locations close to Nicholson Street Tram, Sydney Road Shops and Moreland Station it boasts two car spaces (on title) including undercover garage and a private sunny courtyard.

Description:
Bright and spacious apartment on the banks of Merri Creek.
Filled with natural light, and situated in a quiet, secluded court location overlooking Merri Creek, this over-sized one bedroom apartment boasts approximately 87m2 of living space and places you in the iconic Pentridge estate.
A short walk to Batman train station, trams along Nicholson Street and Sydney Road and Merri Creek bike trails make getting around a breeze, and easy access to the picturesque Coburg Lake, Sydney Road shops and cafes, and the Drive-in Cinema deliver on location and lifestyle.
Situated on the first floor, east-facing floor to ceiling windows take full advantage of the sunrise, and the spacious balcony overlooking Merri Creek is perfect for entertaining and relaxing. With secure underground parking and storage unit, resort-style amenities include communal pool and barbecue area overlooking the park, and automatic gates, intercom system and lift access.
Inside, the space easily switches between airy open-plan living and dining areas that draw the outdoors inside, to cosy seclusion, with double roller blinds, split system heating and cooling and panel heaters providing privacy and comfort.
European appliances and generous bench space define the kitchen, with the bedroom enjoying built-in robes, ensuite bathroom, and an uninterrupted view of parkland.
Clever and ample storage means no compromising on maximal use of space, and separate laundry and powder room cater for convenience and guests.
Internal area: approximately 74m2
Balcony area: approximately 13m2
Total area: approximately 87m2 (plus car space and storage unit)
Phone enquiry code for this property: 6656
